properties.Name: Detonation
properties.Description: The detonation of explosive material in conjunction with a mining activity.

Columns.Name: DetonationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a detonation.

Columns.Name: DetonationLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: MineActivityId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a mine activity.

Columns.Name: BlastInitiationTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp of initiation, which is the act of causing an explosive material to detonate or deflagrate.

Columns.Name: LoadingEndTimestamp
Columns.Description: The end timestamp of loading, which is the placing explosive material in a blasthole or against the material to be blasted.

Columns.Name: LoadingStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The start timestamp of loading, which is the placing explosive material in a blasthole or against the material to be blasted.

Columns.Name: BlastingTechniqueId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a blasting technique.

Columns.Name: InitiatorId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Initiator

Columns.Name: DetonationDepthMeters
Columns.Description: The depth at which the detonation occurs.

Columns.Name: HoleLoadingMethodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a hole loading method.

Columns.Name: BlastingCircuitTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a blasting circuit type.

Columns.Name: DetonationStatusId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a detonation status.

Columns.Name: LoadingFactorRatioNumber
Columns.Description: The weight of explosive per foot in a borehole.

Columns.Name: DelayIntervalSeconds
Columns.Description: The nominal time between the detonations of delay detonators of adjacent periods in a delay series; the nominal time between successive detonations in a blast.

Columns.Name: DelayTimeSeconds
Columns.Description: The lapse of time between the application of a firing signal and the detonation of the base charge of a delay detonator

Columns.Name: DetonatingVelocityFtSecond
Columns.Description: The velocity at which detonation progresses through an explosive in feet/second.

Columns.Name: ExplosiveLoadingFactor
Columns.Description: The amount of explosive used per unit of rock.

Columns.Name: BlastAreaSchema
Columns.Description: A schema depicting the area of a blast within the influence of flying rock missiles, gases, and concussion.

Columns.Name: LoadingFactor
Columns.Description: The weight of explosive per foot in a borehole. (Can be determined by .34 x Borehole diameter squared X density of explosives product).

Columns.Name: PowderFactor
Columns.Description: The ratio of weight of explosive to tons or cubic yards of material blasted.

Columns.Name: DetonationAirblastDecibels
Columns.Description: Airborne shock wave resulting from the detonation of explosives.

Columns.Name: DetonatingPressureGpa
Columns.Description: The pressure created in the reaction zone of a detonating explosive measured ion GPA (gigapascals).

Columns.Name: DetonationGroundVibrationPpv
Columns.Description: Ground movement caused by the stress waves emanating from a blast measured in Peak Particle Velocity.

Columns.Name: MisfireIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates a detonation misfire, which is a blast that fails to detonate completely after an attempt at initiation.

Columns.Name: PrematureFiringIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates a detonation premature firing, which is the detonation of an explosive charge before the intended time.

Columns.Name: MiningActivityDetonationNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the mining activity detonation.
